^ "Le grand-maître s'etait trouvé avec ses chevaliers en 1299 à la reprise de Jerusalem." François Raynouard (1805). "Précis sur les Templiers". 
^ Claudius Jacquand (1846). "Jacques Molay Prend Jerusalem.1299" (painting). Hall of Crusades, Versailles. Retrieved 2007-09-09. 
^ Schein, "Gesta Dei per Mongolos".
^ "Catholic Encyclopedia: Crusades". Newadvent.org. Retrieved 2011-12-19. 
^ Dubarle, André-Marie, «La première captivité de Geoffroy de Charny et l'acquisition du linceul», Montre-nous ton visage, 8, 1993, p. 6-18; «The first captivity of Geoffroy de Charny and the acquisition of the Shroud», rév. et trad. ang. par Daniel C. Scavone, publication électronique
^ "Full text of "A history of the Inquisition of the Middle Ages"". Archive.org. Retrieved 2013-08-21. 
^ ^ Brandon, S. G. F, "Christ in verbal and depicted imagery" in Neusner, Jacob (ed.): Christianity, Judaism and other Greco-Roman cults: Studies for Morton Smith at sixty. Part Two: Early Christianity, pp. 166-167. BRILL, 1975. ISBN 978-90-04-04215-5
^ Barber, The Trial of the Templars, 2nd ed. p. 357 "The account given by the continuator of William Nangis is confirmed by the clerk, Geoffrey of Paris, apparently an eyewitness, who describes Molay as showing no sign of fear and, significantly, as telling those present that God would avenge their deaths."
^ Ferretto of Vicenza, 'Historia rerum in Italia gestarum ab anno 1250 as annum usque 1318', c. 1328, in Malcolm Barber's, The New Knighthood: A History of the Order of the Temple (Cambridge University Press, 1993), pp. 314–315.
^ Henry Charles Lea, A History of The Inquisition of The Middle Ages, Volume 3, page 326 (New York: Cosimo, Inc., 2005, originally published in 1888). ISBN 1-59605-565-0
^ Martin, p. 142.
^ Barber, The New Knighthood, pp. 317–318.
^ First DeMolay. accessed 3/26/2013.
^ DeMolay International. "DeMolay International | History of DeMolay". Demolay.org. Retrieved 2011-12-19. 
^ "The Author of our Ritual: Frank A. Marshall". The DeMolay International website. Retrieved 9 March 2013. 
^ "The Order of DeMolay: Initiatory Degree". (a publication of a DeMolay secret ritual ceremony on the web). The Phoenix Masonry Masonic Museum and Library website. Retrieved 9 March 2013. 
^ "The Order of DeMolay: DeMolay Degree". (a publication of a DeMolay secret ritual ceremony on the web). The Phoenix Masonry Masonic Museum and Library. Retrieved 9 March 2013. 


